    <item>
      <title>Guardian Daily podcast: EU summit on economy; plus police knives crackdown hailed</title>
      <link>http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/blog/audio/2008/dec/12/guardian-daily-podcast</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Chief political correspondent &lt;strong&gt;Nicholas Watt&lt;/strong&gt; reports from Brussels, where EU leaders are hoping to agree on a fiscal stimulus package. Gordon Brown and David Cameron have become embroiled in a split among the governing parties in Germany.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The tiny new democracy of Sark in the Channel Islands votes against  the billionaire Barclay brothers. &lt;strong&gt;Steven Morris&lt;/strong&gt; reports from the island.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Home Office figures show a dramatic fall in the number of young people carrying knives after a police stop-and-search crackdown. &lt;strong&gt;Alexandra Topping&lt;/strong&gt; reports from Hackney, east London.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Woolworths is disappearing from UK high streets after 99 years. We speak to shoppers snapping up bargains at the closing-down sale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://feedads.googleadservices.com/~at/Lha2B_3q59wLui70mg4WgHIpyTI/a"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feedads.googleadservices.com/~at/Lha2B_3q59wLui70mg4WgHIpyTI/i" border="0" ismap="true"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <category domain="http://www.guardian.co.uk/uk">UK news</category>
      <category domain="http://www.guardian.co.uk/world">World news</category>
